children.name: shade x
children.definition: shade/ shading specialized the parts of a picture or painting that the artist has made slightly darker than the other parts : mảng tối
examples: light and shade
a good artist can produce a very realistic effect using onlylight andshade.

children.name: freehand x
children.definition: freehand (of a drawing) drawn by hand without using any special tools : tay không
examples: a freehand sketch/ drawing

children.name: picture a1
children.definition: picture shapes, lines etc painted or drawn on a surface, especially as a piece of art, and often showing what sb or sth looks like
examples: the room had several pictures on the walls.
a book with pictures in it
picture of
i like that picture of the two horses.
draw/paint a/sb’s picture
draw a picture of your house.
he asked her permission to paint her picture(= paint a picture of her).
draw/paint a pictureshe drew a picture of a mushroom on the blackboard.
do a picture of sb/sth(= draw or paint a picture )he’s done a picture of a monster.
a picture hangs somewherethree pictures hung on the wall over his bed.
a picture shows sthformal the picture shows two women leaning down towards a third.
a picture is of sb/sth(= used to talk about what a picture shows )there's a picture of his wife above the fireplace.

children.name: drawing a2
children.definition: drawing a picture that you draw with a pencil, pen etc : bức vẽ
examples: drawing of
a drawing of canterbury cathedral
do/make a drawingsammy was doing a drawing of his sister.
a drawing shows sththe drawing showed a castle surrounded by woods.
a detailed drawinghe made detailed drawings of animals and flowers.
a line drawing(= consisting only of lines) bức vẽ nétthe front cover had a line drawing of a girl on the beach.
a pencil/ink/charcoal etc drawing(= done using a pencil, ink etc )i like to do a few pencil drawings when i go away anywhere.
a scale drawing(= showing the correct relative sizes of things )the architect made a scale drawing of the new room.

children.name: painting a2
children.definition: paintinga picture made using paint :
examples: the painting now hangs in the museum of modern art.
a collection of valuable paintings
painting of
picasso did several paintings of her.
there was a large painting of his father on the wall.

children.name: doodle x
children.definition: doodle a drawing of shapes, lines, or patterns that you do when you are thinking about something else or when you are bored: vẽ nguệch ngoạc
examples: by the end of the lecture the back of my book was covered in little doodles.

children.name: stick figure x
children.definition: stick figure/ matchstick figure a simple picture of a person in which the head is drawn as a circle and the body, arms and legs are drawn as lines : tranh người que

children.name: cartoon a2
children.definition: cartoon afunnydrawing, especially in a newspaper or a magazine, often with a joke written under it: tranh biếm họa, hoạt hình
examples: the cartoon shows a group of elephants trying to get into a phone-box.
a satirical cartoon that appears in the washington post
a political / editorial cartoon
political cartoons are often very cruel.
cartoon/ comicstrip[c] a series of pictures drawn inside boxes that tell a story
charles schultz was famous for his cartoon strip about snoopy and charlie brown.
the ‘peanuts’ cartoon strip was created by charles m. schulz.

children.name: scribble x
children.definition: scribble a drawing of lines, shapes etc that look untidy and have no particular pattern, shape, or picture - use this especially about what small children do before they can draw or write properly: hình vẽ nguệch ngoạc
examples: how am i going to get all these scribbles off the wallpaper?

children.name: sketch c1
children.definition: sketch  a picture consisting of a few lines drawn quickly with a pen or pencil : bức phác họa, phác thảo
examples: sketch of
i thought your sketches of the garden were very attractive.
he did some rough sketches of the costumes.
quick/ rough sketch
cantor drew a rough sketch of his apartment on a napkin.
gabriella did a quick sketch of her baby daughter.
i’ve done a rough sketch of how to get to the church.
do/make a sketch
the architect did a sketch of how the building will look when it’s finished.

children.name: caricature x
children.definition: caricature a funny drawing of sb that makes them look silly: tranh biếm họa
examples: he is famous for his caricatures of politicans.
we had our caricatures drawn by a street artist while we were on vacation in turkey.
caricature of
caricatures of politicians.
politicians are used to having caricatures of themselves printed in newspapers.
figurativeover the years he's become a grotesque caricatureofhimself.
draw a caricature
she draws caricatures of well-known politicians.

children.name: print c1
children.definition: printa copy of a painting that is produced by taking a photograph of it and printing it onto paper : bản chụp (của một bức vẽ)
examples: a limited edition of lithographic prints by john lennon

children.name: canvas x
children.definition: canvas a painting done with oil paints on a canvas : tranh sơn dầu
examples: these two canvases by hockney would sell for £500 000.
the gallery has a canvas by paul cézanne.

children.name: old master x
children.definition: old master a painting by one of a famous painter, especially from the 15th to 18th century :bức hoạ của một hoạ sĩ bậc thầy
examples: a priceless collection of old masters

children.name: watercolour x
children.definition: watercolouruk/watercolorus a picture painted with watercolours : tranh màu nước, tranh thuỷ mặc
examples: some lovely watercolours

children.name: oil painting x
children.definition: oil painting a picture painted with oil paints : tranh sơn dầu
examples: he wanted to take a look at the wall paintings in the church.

children.name: print c1
children.definition: print a picture that is made by cutting lines onto a piece of metal or wood and then printing it onto paper : bản rập

children.name: illustration c1
children.definition: illustration a picture in a book, article etc, especially one that helps you to understand it:tranh minh họa
examples: the new encyclopedia is full of color illustrations and photographs.
who did the illustrations for the book? they’re lovely.

children.name: tracing x
children.definition: tracing a copy of a drawing or pattern made by drawing over it through a piece of thin transparent paper : bản can
examples: he made a tracingofthe picture.

children.name: stencil x
children.definition: stencil picture made by drawing or painting through the holes in such a piece of card, etc. onto a surface : bản in từ khuôn tô
examples: stencil of
she did a stencilofa rainbow on her daughter's bedroom wall.

children.name: mosaic x
children.definition: mosaic a pattern or picture made using many small pieces of coloured stone or glass : tranh khảm
examples: a beautiful 10th century mosaic
figurativethe country is now a cultural and social mosaic (= mixture) due to the influx of different ethnic groups.

children.name: lithograph x
children.definition: lithograph a picture printed using a stone or metal block on which an image has been drawn with a thick oily substance that attracts ink : tờ in đá; in thạch bản

children.name: engraving x
children.definition: engraving a picture printed onto paper from a piece of wood or metal into which the design has been cut : ản in khắc, tranh khắc
examples: metal / wood engraving

children.name: collage x
children.definition: collage a picture in which various materials or objects, for example paper, cloth or photographs, are stuck onto a larger surface : tranh cắt dán
examples: the children made a collage of postcards.

children.name: etching x
children.definition: etching a picture produced by printing from a metal plate which has been etched with acid: bản khắc a-xít

children.name: aquatint x
children.definition: aquatinta picture produced by cutting it into a copper sheet with acid and then printing it: tranh khắc a-xít
examples: an aquatint by picasso

children.name: pastel x
children.definition: pastel a picture made by using pastels : bức tranh vẽ bằng phấn màu
examples: the show includes eighty-five paintings, pastels and sculptures.

children.name: fresco x
children.definition: fresco a painting made on a wall while the plaster is still wet : tranh nề
examples: michelangelo's famous frescoes are in the sistine chapel in rome.

children.name: mural x
children.definition: mural a painting that is painted on a wall, either inside or outside a building: bích hoạ
examples: murals depicting aesop's fables

children.name: wall painting x
children.definition: wall painting a picture that has been painted directly onto a wall, especially a fresco
examples: he wanted to take a look at the wall paintings in the church.
